Eventually they didn’t open at all. Swatch told me on Thursday how they “are expecting huge demand”, yet failed to implement any kind of security, crowd management or a queuing and ticketing system. The sort of thing Apple set the standard for for years. https://t.co/2UKHPU2cf5
@Motorscribe Yes that seems likely
@CamBunton @christhall Can’t wait for those prices to crash when it gets restocked and available online too.
@IanMorris78 @davidchow @CamBunton @christhall Yup. Was just the same at Covent Garden and Oxford Street too. I heard each store has about 140 units. Staff seemed unsure about how to open.
@neilmbriscoe @Stuart_Craigie @SwatchUK Completely mad situation. I gave up and headed home
@chashallett Completely insane isn’t it. I miss my Speedmaster but won’t pay over retail for a Swatch
Reader, I gave up. Glad I did as well, as the queue stretched around an entire block and doubled back on itself. Staff seemed unsure how best to open the shop.
@londongecko Yep I’ve heard exactly that too. There are always some who will pay a massive premium to get one early, but resale prices will surely nosedive once restocks and online sales happen.
@HunterSkipworth Agreed. Surely Swatch will want to capitalise on the popularity and mass-produce it. Then resale prices will collapse. Quite nice being up and in town early!
@WilkinLee Yeah if it’s not limited then we’ll get one eventually and the resale prices will collapse.
@HunterSkipworth Feels unfair doesn’t it. I heard only 140 or so units per store elsewhere, so imagine 90% here will be disappointed. Store restocks and online availability should be happening later
@jameselmer73 @NaomiPanter Haha! If I’d thought ahead I would have come into town for drinks last night and brought a blanket
@wwodb Oh yeah, I’m sure the initial resell prices will be ridiculous. A few hundred quid profit will be worth a night queueing for many people.
This, basically. I hope there are some genuine Swatch fans near the front, but I suspect most Moonswatches are being bought to be sold. https://t.co/oaDOaEMgie
@tmjackson I’ve a feeling you’re right. Swatch has said there will be a store restock and online sales seem likely too. Hype prices will surely fall once that happens.
8:15am. 45 minutes until we can all have our assumptions confirmed and told to go home. Still, nice to get up early on a weekend isn’t it?
@wwodb Quite. This will fuel the hype and probably make buying one online (at retail price) tricky too

@pumactr I used to report on the iPhone queues and they were often fun, friendly events. Then the reselling started, driven by demand from countries that got new releases later, and it completely changed.
@Stuart_Craigie Yeah I saw those numbers too. I reckon 100 units wouldn’t even cover those who look like they’ve queued all night
@jameselmer73 @NaomiPanter Indeed, and I’m now in the sun so it could be worse. Thanks!

@richardaucock I heard about that! The queue has moved forward a couple of times but I’m fairly certain I’ll be going home empty-handed. I heard they’ll be restocked and potentially sold online later too.

‘Retail is Broken’
That’s the headline.
